        "content": "<h3>Below are reviews of the top 3dCart alternatives and competitors:</h3>\n\n<p><u><strong><a href=\"https://virtocommerce.com/glossary/shopify-alternatives\">Shopify </a></strong></u>is one of the popular 3dcart competitors. Shopify is popular with B2C customers all over the world for its intuitive design and simple interface. A wide variety of tools and extensions is also offered through Shopify&#39;s unique AppStore to help you to broaden your website&#39;s feature base.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>A major downside of Shopify is its inability to successfully market products on the Web. Another factor you should consider before you choose this platform is that it is closed source (proprietary) and requires a significant amount of money to be invested into it. On the other hand, you don&#39;t have to dig deep into its code in order to customize your website. The easy drag and drop functionality will help to quickly set up without any programming involved. Shopify&#39;s customer support is outstanding and will gladly help you along the way of creating your web store.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Keep in mind though that despite its wonderful features, Shopify is hard to scale and customize, due to its closed source origin, and may not be the right choice for enterprise and B2B ecommerce. Many businesses outgrow Shopify, and have to go through an expensive and time consuming replatforming exercise.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><u><strong>Volusion:</strong></u> Another great alternative to 3dcart is Volusion. Just like Shopify, it is closed source. If you are tech savvy, this platform will impress you with its expandability and functionality. The downside is in content marketing functionality (or rather lack of thereof) and design templates as Volusion does not offer many.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>What this 3dcart alternative does offer though is a vast knowledge base that can help you with all kinds of questions, as well as guide you through the process of creating your perfect store. Just li